headline.main: DAVIES IN SEATTLE WITH STALIN REPLY; On Way to Give Soviet Premier's Message to Roosevelt, He Stops Overnight on Coast FLIGHT BACK VIA SIBERIA Plane Left Moscow Saturday -- Weather Bars Cross-Canada Trip From Alaska

lead_paragraph: SEATTLE, June 1 (AP) -- Joseph E. Davies, President Roosevelt's emissary to Joseph Stalin, arrived here today en route to report to the President in Washington, it was announced by Major Frank E. Williamson, commanding the Air Transport and Control Detachsent.
abstract: Davies-Stalin conf: Davies arrives, Seattle, on way to rept to Roosevelt
